<item>
            <title>[JDK-8301988] VerifyLiveClosure::verify_liveness asserts on bad pointers outside heap</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8301988</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>G1 uses this closure to verify object references. It has the following issues:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- it uses decode_not_null which will assert if the given oop address is not in the heap, making the remainder of the verification useless in that case&lt;br/&gt;
- if the referenced object is not in the heap, we try to get its heap region too when printing, which also fails some assertions&lt;br/&gt;
- in the innermost if lots of code is duplicated in both cases&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Fix these issues.</description>
